<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
   <head>
       <title>2nd practical</title>
       <style>
           p {
               color: blue;
               background-color: gold;
           }
   
           #id-sel {
               color: red;
               background-color: black;
           }
   
           .para-class {
               color: white;
               background-color: green;
           }
       </style>
   </head>

   <body>
       <h1>Demonstration of element selector, ID selector, Class selector</h1>
       <p>Element selector apply to every single element on the web page.</p>
       <p>The effect will be applied to every paragraph.
           The back ground color is set to gold and text color is blue.</p>
       <div id="id-sel">The id selector uses the id attribute of an
           HTML element to select a specific element.
           The id of an element should be unique within
          a page, so the id selector is used to select
           one unique element!
           To select an element with a specific id, write
           a hash (#) character, followed by the id of the
           element.
       </div>
       <p class="para-class">The class selector selects elements with a specific
           class attribute.
           To select elements with a specific class, write a
           period (.) character, followed by the name of the
           class.</p>
   </body>

</html>
